	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have quested most of the pieces by myself without much help or a guild.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have the BP, gauntlets, boots, 1 bracer and the vambraces.  true the BP is the easiest piece to get. the others really are not that difficult if you get a group and have the time.  are the quest fair on the task/reward system that is in place? that is a matter of opinon.  when one remembers that there were alot of players who fought hard for equipable armor for iksar sk's above banded and got the dreadscale armor created. should the ragefire portion of the cleric epic be taken out because most clerics can't complete it? i got gracnist skull by asking a higher level player who was camping grac for the totem and earing to loot the skull because it was a qust item that i needed. there are some nice players who will let you loot the no-drop items if you ask them nicely.<br>True there are some players who just have a really high guildmate kill everything to get the quest items, but some of us just have time and determination to get the items that we need. probably the easiest way to get the boots would be to get in a group and camp a sarnak ruin in OT until Zorash spawns and drops the boots. Hope that you get your greaves as i plan too also.<br><br>P.S. all iksar quest armor (Dreadscale,Scaled Mystic, Trooper Scale) has one piece that is a pain to get. unfortunately for dread it's the greaves.<br><br>Conton Darkbander<br>Iksar Shadow Knight 33rd season<br>Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
